 		&lt;/testPlanLibraries&gt;
 2. Place a copy of [*log4j2.xml* file][4] to `src/test/conf` folder of your Maven project and [configure JMeter logging][5] according to your requirements. Make sure to add Logstash appender to it like:

        &lt;appender name=&quot;STASH&quot; class=&quot;ch.qos.logback.core.rolling.RollingFileAppender&quot;&gt;
            &lt;file&gt;/desired/location/of/the/log/file&lt;/file&gt;
            &lt;rollingPolicy class=&quot;ch.qos.logback.core.rolling.TimeBasedRollingPolicy&quot;&gt;
                &lt;fileNamePattern&gt;/desired/location/of/the/log/file.%d{yyyy-MM-dd}.log&lt;/fileNamePattern&gt;
                &lt;maxHistory&gt;7&lt;/maxHistory&gt;
            &lt;/rollingPolicy&gt;
            &lt;encoder class=&quot;net.logstash.logback.encoder.LogstashEncoder&quot;/&gt;
        &lt;/appender&gt;
        &lt;root level=&quot;DEBUG&quot;&gt;
            &lt;appender-ref ref=&quot;STASH&quot;/&gt;
        &lt;/root&gt;

 3. That should be it, you can not point the `logback.xml` to read the configured file(s), convert the output to JSON and feed ELK stack with the data 


